    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>131400</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><orig>ετ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="1a"/><space quantity="1" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="ἀπό">ἀφ᾿</w> <w lemma="ὅς1" type="relative">οὗ</w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><lb n="3" break="no"/><orig>τωμ</orig> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="4"/><orig>μελ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="5"/><orig>ολ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="5a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem><orig>ετ</orig></lem>
                        <rdg>ἔτ<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></rdg>
                        <rdg><note>or</note> <seg part="I">ἐτ<supplied reason="lost">ιμ</supplied></seg></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>This looks like a dossier bearing at least two documents, of which we would have the end of the first and the beginning of the second. The beginning 
               of the second seems to recall past events 'Since the time when…'. Hence the idea of a royal letter. But this should remain highly hypothetical.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
